OL,6,FHe "would have categorically said that
OL,7,Fwas not a match" if he had been.
OL,9,FIn her report, Ms Whittle said
OL,10,Ffailings with the risk assessment
OL,11,Fprocess meant there was "no evidence"
OL,12,Fthe possible dangers to the foster
OL,13,Fcarers and the other child in their
OL,14,Fcare "had been considered or assessed".
OL,16,FRotherham Council has been approached
OL,17,Ffor comment.
